text: Lastly, I'd highly recommend just knowing your local charts and platforms well. It will take reading up and/or following the right accs, but it goes a long way in helping you figure out what works for you and which platforms you want to devote how much time/energy/money to 👍

name: Lilac⁷ 💜
text: But as long as we ensure we don't cross boundaries by demanding changes to the art for a record, or stressing other ARMYs out with panicked posts or guilt-tripping...I think we'll be okay ☺️

name: Lilac⁷ 💜
text: I think we can do a good job of maintaining that balance. Like we have every reason n right to criticize YT as a platform (don't confuse that as discouragement to stream). Keep streaming at the pace that works for you, set goals n streaming parties if that's what motivates you...

name: Lilac⁷ 💜
text: Abt YT, I think as long as we don't lean towards either extreme...we're good. Like don't reduce the art to just numbers/figures or don't treat the YT records as more imp than the art...but don't abandon the platform or reduce streaming at whatever pace you can, either

name: Lilac⁷ 💜
text: @Daechwita__D2 Ahh I see...yes perhaps. I've seen this dissatisfaction esp with those who complain 'but they didn't make music like this before'. I guess the healthiest way to move on is listen to what you like, don't listen to what you don't like, or just unstan

name: Lilac⁷ 💜
text: @fku_nduropinion I agree with you...I've seen an argument brought up a few times abt how some feel entitled to ask for those changes or preferences because they're 'paying customers' but while that applies to a set product/service, I think the same logic can't apply to art

text: @Daechwita__D2 I'm sorry I don't think I fully understand your comment. Are you equating fan created content with fans dictating the artist's art? Cause that's what I'm currently taking away. Would love if you could elaborate :)

name: Lilac⁷ 💜
text: @fku_nduropinion 💜

name: Lilac⁷ 💜
text: The whole point of art is to engage with a perspective or message the artist wishes to convey. Restricting the artist to what you want or how you want it defeats the whole purpose and potential of art

name: Lilac⁷ 💜
text: Our decisions end at the choice to engage or not engage with the art/artist. We can support it if we want, or disengage if we dislike it. But to go so far as to make demands or dictate preferred ways in which we'd like the art to be made? That's definitely crossing a boundary

name: Lilac⁷ 💜
text: I think a crucial boundary is separating our thoughts n feelings abt someone's art, from translating those thoughts/feelings to demands & assumptions of the artist. The former is very valid, the latter however, is not our right as fans imo...even if we're paying patrons https://t.co/Is8vMV9Ipb

name: Lilac⁷ 💜
text: All 3 unit stages for me...the circular stage that made for such seamless transitions, to the very detailed set design, outfits and themes (like time-in-motion for Jamais Vu, disco throwback for Respect and revisiting vmin's history in Friends). It was perfect 👏 https://t.co/9O5SsaBJhe

name: Lilac⁷ 💜
text: Our boys are world-class artists delivering only the best content. They could've easily done this show from a free space like their office or home to reduce costs...but they chose to give us a high quality production instead. Pls keep these factors in mind too

name: Lilac⁷ 💜
text: This. I was particularly impressed with the detailed set designs (and the fact that they had nearly one for each song). They pulled some big budget stuff today...and we always say pay IF you can, but if you can't there will be those looking out for you via a livestream or GA 💜 https://t.co/2BSV5GNpBB

name: Lilac⁷ 💜
text: There's a lot to unravel abt every performance because there's so much thought, intentional design choices + detail incorporated into each one. But I also had a great time on the TL - the collective screams, super quick translations, the crying, virtual hugs...I felt connected ☺️

name: Lilac⁷ 💜

name: Lilac⁷ 💜
text: And since their energy is always perfectly suited for a studio or stadium, I wonder if this was in fact different or just a lot more apparent given the online nature of today's show. Either way it's left a very lasting impression and performances we're gonna be revisiting a LOT

name: Lilac⁷ 💜
text: Stil can't get over BTS' energy today. It wasn't over enthusiastic...it was smooth, seamless n relaxed. They made intricate choreo + synchronisation look almost effortless. I can't explain it but they had this charismatic aura that reached us well beyond an online interface

text: We went from finding multiple existing fundraising opportunities (the fact that multiple ARMY-led ones already existed speaks volumes), to choosing one to focus all our energy on within an hour or so, and investing others beyond our community to participate within a day...WOW

name: Lilac⁷ 💜
text: That's why it was so easy to align on a single idea and HT...we already wanted to do this, we already had been doing this individually, and so putting a goal to it was just a perfect catalyst (you know how we love our goals and trackers ☺️)

name: Lilac⁷ 💜
text: I'm so amazed but unsurprised at how quickly ARMY managed to rally together to raise what we have so far. We didn't need any convincing...the intent, the values, the network already exists n we just needed to leverage one another the same way we've done for various causes before

name: Lilac⁷ 💜
text: And this is in no way meant to take away from the real vision of this donation drive, I'm just seeing a lot of curious locals both on here and irl and was hoping we could continue the good work while also patiently engaging with those asking us questions 💜

name: Lilac⁷ 💜
text: While it certainly is unfair that we're often misjudged, I think locals have been fed a very misguided image of us and end up generalising us. Let's educate them and engage in their curiosity. I'm sure many of them are fascinated with what they're seeing rn and are just curious

name: Lilac⁷ 💜
text: Fam so a few of my local friends saw the match a million news and have been asking a ton of questions. One of them asked what a stan was and I realised he had an extremely uninformed view of who a BTS stan is. I'm guessing there will be more on twt, let's be patient with them? ☺️

name: Lilac⁷ 💜
text: Lastly I'd like to add that this is only wrt the organised network of anti accs we've seen try to take the boys down over and over again...not ARMY who've raised legitimate concerns. We need to be thoughtful and be careful of not bundling up everything as anti behaviour

name: Lilac⁷ 💜
text: And perhaps the hardest part of it all - call your moots out if you need to, I soft block or even block those who've ended up moving like antis or given them a platform in the past

name: Lilac⁷ 💜
text: We need to organise, be more strategic and control ourselves from responding to antis. Find accs you trust, make GCs with them, silently exchange reporting content with them, vet all accs + info you see, observe acc behaviour...there's so much we can do 👍

name: Lilac⁷ 💜
text: Also I'd like to add that when we say 'ignore antis and trolls' we don't mean let's not do anything abt it. We mean don't engage or give them free publicity, while still silently reporting and blocking them until they no longer have a platform to spew their hate

name: Lilac⁷ 💜
text: I couldn't think of a less cornier way to put it 🙈 But I meant every word

text: I've been thinking abt this a lot and I really do want to improve and be a better ally. The first thing I've decided is to not react in the heat of the moment and listen more instead. Pls call me out again if you think I need it, I'm not perfect but I simply need to do better

name: Lilac⁷ 💜
text: Fam I'm so sorry if I disregarded your feelings or concerns in any way. I was given much-needed perspective by a black ARMY and realised that in being consumed by my rage towards a group of ppl, I didn't stop to think of others whose feelings I was ignoring in the process 😔

name: Lilac⁷ 💜
text: @Brie__yonce Honestly given the situation we find ourselves in, we all just need to do better. No one's perfect and we are learning. And yes, will certainly do so. Thanks again for helping me out :)

name: Lilac⁷ 💜
text: @theyoongiggle I did not in any way intend to paint everyone with the same anti brush. I was directing my anger towards a specific group of known antis and I had just gone through hundreds of spam accs weaponizing a sensitive situation to fuel a witchhunt. But I def appreciate the perspective

name: Lilac⁷ 💜
text: @theyoongiggle Hi thank you so much for what you shared. I've been giving this a lot of thought and I completely see where you are coming from. I was consumed with rage towards a specific group of antis in that moment and I didn't stop to consider the feelings of those who had valid concerns

name: Lilac⁷ 💜
text: @Brie__yonce I'm reflecting & working on being a better ally and the first thing I'm going to start doing is not react in the heat of the moment and just listen. Thanks for sharing what you did, it served as the mirror I definitely needed 💜

name: Lilac⁷ 💜
text: @Brie__yonce Hi Brie, I've thought a lot about what you said and I wanted to say I'm so terribly sorry for disregarding your feelings and concerns.
